{"word":"Caesarea","slug":"caesarea","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Caesarea</b> A seaport in Palestine.<br/> Home of:<br/> - Philip<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=8&verse=40'>Act 8:40</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=21&verse=8'>Act 21:8</a> <br/> - Cornelius, the centurion<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=10&verse=1'>Act 10:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=10&verse=24'>Act 10:24</a> <br/> - Herod<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=12&verse=23'>Act 12:23</a> <br/> - Felix<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=23&verse=24'>Act 23:24</a> <br/> Paul conveyed to:<br/> - By the disciples to save him from his enemies<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=9&verse=30'>Act 9:30</a> <br/> - By Roman soldiers to be tried by Felix<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=23&verse=35'>Act 23:35</a> "}]}